{% block content %}

    <h1>Gutter Cleaning in Coquitlam — Protect Your Tri-Cities Home from Water Damage</h1>
    
    <p>Coquitlam's location at the base of the mountains, surrounded by dense forests and experiencing heavy Pacific rainfall, creates ideal conditions for clogged gutters. Leaves, pine needles, moss, and organic debris accumulate quickly in drainage systems, especially during fall and winter months. When gutters become blocked, water overflows onto fascia boards, siding, and foundations — leading to costly repairs that could have been prevented with regular maintenance.</p>

    <p>Clean Gutters Crew (CGC) provides professional gutter cleaning throughout Coquitlam to help homeowners stay ahead of moisture-related damage. We understand how local weather patterns and tree coverage affect homes in this part of the Tri-Cities, from established neighbourhoods to newer developments.</p>

    <p>We serve all Coquitlam areas including Burke Mountain, Westwood Plateau, Ranch Park, Eagle Ridge, Harbour Chines, Cape Horn, Maillardville, Austin Heights, and surrounding communities. Homes backing onto forested areas or ravines typically require more frequent maintenance, and our team is fully equipped to handle those high-debris environments safely and efficiently.</p>

    <h2>Why Coquitlam Homes Need Regular Gutter Maintenance</h2>
    <p>Coquitlam receives significant rainfall throughout the year, and the city's proximity to mountains and forests means constant exposure to organic debris. For homeowners in their 30s, 40s, 50s, and beyond, maintaining gutters is essential for protecting your investment. Blocked gutters can cause:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Roof leaks and shingle damage</li>
        <li>Rotting fascia and soffit boards</li>
        <li>Foundation cracks and basement moisture</li>
        <li>Mold growth in hidden areas</li>
        <li>Landscape erosion around the home</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What Sets Us Apart in Coquitlam</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Experience with mountain-adjacent and forested properties</li>
        <li>Fully insured and safety-focused team</li>
        <li>Eco-friendly cleaning methods</li>
        <li>Flexible scheduling including weekends</li>
        <li>Transparent pricing starting at $180 for standard homes</li>
        <li>Special consideration for seniors and repeat customers</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our Professional Gutter Cleaning Process</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Visual inspection and assessment of problem areas</li>
        <li>Safe, thorough removal of all debris by hand and vacuum</li>
        <li>Complete downspout clearing and flow testing</li>
        <li>Inspection for cracks, rust, loose joints, and wear</li>
        <li>Before-and-after photos on request</li>
        <li>Clean worksite — no mess left behind</li>
    </ol>

    <p>The entire service typically takes 1-3 hours depending on home size and gutter condition. We work carefully to protect your roof, landscaping, and exterior surfaces.</p>

    <h2>Seasonal Considerations for Coquitlam</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Fall — Heavy leaf drop from deciduous trees</li>
        <li>Winter — Continuous rain and potential ice buildup</li>
        <li>Spring — Pollen, seed pods, and storm debris</li>
        <li>Year-round — Pine needles and moss in forested areas</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Most Coquitlam homes benefit from cleaning at least twice per year — once in late fall after leaves drop and once in spring before heavy rains. Properties near Burke Mountain or surrounded by tall conifers may need additional service.</p>

    <p>Regular gutter maintenance is one of the simplest ways to protect your Coquitlam home from unnecessary water damage and preserve its long-term value.</p>

    <p><strong>Contact us today for your free estimate and keep your Tri-Cities home safe and dry.</strong></p>

